Text View Features

  • Hover over a tag button in the sidebar to highlight tagged words in the text view.
  • The reverse works, too: Hover over words to highlight their tag in the sidebar (or wait for a tooltip to appear).
  • Clicking on a tag adds a persistent highlight color to tagged words.
  • All "persistently highlighted" tags and words use that same light-blue background color (for now), unless a URI parameter provides a custom color (and later, weighting) for one or more tags.

Arrow Key Shortcuts

To use these shortcuts, first click somewhere inside the text view.

  • Press the down arrow when you're at the bottom of a page to go to the next page.
  • Press the up arrow when you're at the top of a page to go to the previous page.
  • Press the left or right arrow key to move to the previous or next page, respectively.
